1. What is dataguard ?

=> its a oracle feature, it is based on replication and this feature provides 3 important 
factors. i>. High Avalibility (HA), ii>. Disaster Recovery (DR), iii>. Data Protection (DP)

Data Protection (DP),  —  Anyhow, we can’t afford any data losses. 
High Availability (HA),  — it will be available 24x7, so it connects to the database.
Disaster Recovery (DR). — natural calamities, power outrage then it will use.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

2. Why we use dataguard when we do the recovery & restore from backup ?

=> reason is, 
one, if any natarual calamities occured then it hard to restore our backup.
two, if our backup has other server and backup size too large (30-50tb) it hard to restore
   because it will take too much time. 	
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

3. Maximumm how many standby DB we can create ?
=> 30 standby database.
