4. How many types of standby database ?
=> 3 standby DB. Physical standby, logical standby, snapshot standby.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

5. Physical Standby --

=> all redo data is moving to primary to physical standby. jo bhi datafiles mein blocks hain 
	woh move to physical standby. which is consider as block by block copy.

=> Exact block by block copy of primary database.
	Synchronous or Asynchronous update.
	Open mode - READ_ONLY mode
	Same DBID will having in physical standby. 

=> Benifites -- 

	- it's having data protection.
	- deaster recovery and high avalavility solution.
	- if primary down then we can make standby as primary.
	- if backup job running and it take too much time consuming and resources that occures sloness of the database. so, overcome this situation we can run RMAN job in standby.


--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

6. Logical Standby --

=> 	It'll apply SQL statment primary to standby database. it's not that much consistant as physical standby. 

=> Benifites --
	- DBID is diffrent.
	- READ_ONLY as well as READ,WRITE mode.
	- there can be some additional database objects (table,indexs,synnonym)

=> Purpose of using this --

	- Doing some analysis purposes.
	- Create some additional database object we can use it.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

7. Snapshot Standby --

=> if we are go for testing (parameter change), can we apply parameter changes(increase size) in the directly primary database ? no right. 
We've to do this low envirment like, UAT,TEST. In this kind of senario we use 'Snapshot standby' database. 

If in 'SNAPSHOT STANDBY' we don't do any changes it consider as a 'PHYSICAL STANDBY'.
As soon as we do any changes it will become 'SNAPSHOT STANDBY'.

👉 Flashback -- This snapshot standby having the feature call 'FLASHBACK'. 

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

