11. What is failover and switchover ?
 
👉 Switcover -- Basically this is a pland activity. For example - if i doing some patching activity, upgradation we need to DB down, listner stop right. So, we can't afford 
these on production database. So, we move primary to standby. so, we can do all activity on 
standby database. This Role Reversal process called 'Switchover'.

👉 Failover -- This is a unplaned activity. if primary got crashed then standby convert as a primary.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

12. What is LNS server process ?
=> LNS (Log writer Network Service) is a background process it will residing on primary side.

👉 Purpose -- 

LNS is moving/replicating all the redo entries primary to standby over a network. If LNS network is down won't be replicate primary to standby.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

13. how many background process on primary side ?

=> 6 BG process. 👉 LNS / 👉 LGWR  / 👉 ARCn / 👉 DBwn / 👉 CKPT / 👉 PMON

📌 LNS - LNS is moving/replicating all the redo entries primary to standby over a network.

📌 LGWR - it writes redo entries redo log buffer to online redo log file.

📌 ARCn - It create archive copies of online redo log file.

📌 DBWn - writes all dirty blocks from buffer cacahe to datafiles.

📌 CKPT - Intructs DBwn to update control file.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

14. How many background process on standby side ?

=> 5 BG process. - 👉 RFS / 👉 MRP / 👉 LSP  / 👉 FAL /  👉 SMON /  👉 PMON


📌 RFS (Remote File Server) : Recives all redo streams which coming from Primary. 

	👉 RFS receive karke 'Standby Redo Log' Files (SRL) pe likhta hai!
	👉 Main reciver process of DG.
	👉 Always running on standby

📌 MRP (Manage Recovery Process) : 

If database is 'physical standby' db then 'MRP' will apply all archives in physical standby database. Apply redo data on physical standby.

	👉 MRP start command - 
	ALTER DATABASE RECOVER MANAGED STANDBY DATABASE USING CURRENT LOGFILE DISCONNECT;


📌 LSP (Logical Standby Process) : 

It convert all redo data to SQL and then apply it to standby.
If database is 'logical standby' db then 'LSP' will apply all archives in logical standby database.

📌 FAL (Fetch Archive Log) : 

If any archive gap occures on standby then FAL automatically fetch missing archive logs
from primary. 

	👉 FAL Parameters - FAL_SERVER = Primary
			       FAL_CLIENT = Standby
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

15. What is RFS Process ?

👉 RFS (Remote File Server) : This RFS recived the data (redo entries) which coming from primary side and share by LNS in the standby side, and applying it to standby database.

👉 main recive process of DataGuard.
👉 Always running in standby database.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

16. Sync and Async & Affirm and Noaffirm parameter diffrence ?

👉 Async - LNS carry data from redo log file (disk).

👉 Noaffirm - Not getting any acknowledgment from standby db. It won't required any confirmation. 

👉 Sync - LNS carry data from redo log file buffer (memory).

👉 Affirm - It wait for the acknowledgment for the redo to be written into disk.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

