20. Snapshot and Active DG diffrent ?
 
✅ Snapshot --

👉 STEP 1:
Physical Standby chal raha hai, MRP apply kar raha hai

👉 STEP 2:
Convert to Snapshot Standby:
--MRP STOP ho jaata hai
--Guaranteed Restore Point
automatically banta hai!
--DB READ-WRITE open hota hai!

👉 STEP 3:
--Dev/Test team kaam karte hain:
--INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE, DDL
Sab allowed! ✅
--Primary se Redo aa raha hai
but APPLY nahi ho raha! ⚠️

👉 STEP 4:
Testing complete!
Convert back to Physical Standby:
Restore Point pe Flashback!
Testing data GONE! ✅
MRP wapas start! ✅
Redo apply resume! ✅

✅ Commands -- 

-- Physical → Snapshot:
DGMGRL> CONVERT DATABASE 'STANDBY' TO SNAPSHOT STANDBY;

-- Ya SQL se:
SQL> ALTER DATABASE CONVERT TO SNAPSHOT STANDBY;

-- Verify:
SELECT DB_UNIQUE_NAME,DATABASE_ROLE,OPEN_MODE FROM V$DATABASE;

-- DATABASE_ROLE = SNAPSHOT STANDBY
-- OPEN_MODE     = READ WRITE 

-- Snapshot → Physical wapas:
DGMGRL> CONVERT DATABASE 'STANDBY' TO PHYSICAL STANDBY;

-- Testing data automatically GONE! 
-- MRP apply resume! 


✅ Active DG (ADG) -- Reporting purpose we use. Generating reports. AWS,ASH report.

Physical Standby: DQL only.
READ-ONLY + MRP APPLY dono!

Primary pe:
Redo generate hota hai

Standby pe:
MRP real-time apply karta hai
AND Users DQL queries kar sakte hain!

Real-time updated data read kar sakte hain! 

✅ Commands:

-- ADG start karo:
-- Standby ko READ ONLY open karo:
👉 SQL> ALTER DATABASE OPEN READ ONLY;

-- MRP apply bhi start karo:
👉 SQL> ALTER DATABASE RECOVER MANAGED STANDBY DATABASE USING CURRENT LOGFILE DISCONNECT;

-- Verify:
👉 SELECT DB_UNIQUE_NAME,DATABASE_ROLE,OPEN_MODE FROM V$DATABASE;

-- DATABASE_ROLE = PHYSICAL STANDBY
-- OPEN_MODE     = READ ONLY WITH APPLY 

-- MRP check:
👉 SELECT PROCESS, STATUS FROM V$MANAGED_STANDBY WHERE PROCESS = 'MRP0';
-- STATUS = APPLYING_LOG 
